I get asked fairly often about how we are able to make progress as quickly as we do in business. ⁣
⁣
I’m also asked how we’re able to maintain such a strong culture as we scale to the levels we have over the past few years. ⁣
⁣
This picture is a great example of how these things are not just possible but almost guaranteed. This is a picture of one of my best friends and advisors @jaydoran_thecultureman reading one of the books given to him for Christmas this afternoon at my house. Putting in the work while others enjoy each other’s company on Christmas. ⁣
⁣
He’s reading a 700+ page book on business strategy and principles that he started reading immediately after receiving it as a gift. Notice all the Christmas mayhem that remains around him as he reads...yet NOTHING stops his focus. ⁣
⁣
10 adults and 4 children running around my house today with all the noise you might expect from a Christmas Day celebration of that size…and Jay is hundreds of pages in learning information we will use in the days, months, and sometimes years ahead. ⁣
⁣
It’s the things that people do that nobody sees that truly separate the good from the GREAT. The hours spent STUDYING long after we’re done with “formal education” are what allows the best to be the best. ⁣
⁣
This is a picture of one of the GOATS of his craft. 🐐🐐🐐 This guy has brought insane value to my life in more ways than I can describe. Today and everyday, I’m grateful for this guy…and for anyone I meet on my journey that are committed to constant self improvement at this level.⁣
⁣
Merry Christmas brother!!! Thank you for your friendship, for your example, for always challenging me to be my absolute best, and for all the knowledge and joy you bring to my life and to my family.

VC2Art: Exhibit 1 this Saturday at Stage AE!

Athletic Aesthetic: Exhibit 1 is a live in-person, interactive art experience that is designed to encourage current/former athletes as well as fans of the game to connect in a new way.

This event will feature the entire "HIM Collection" from Pittsburgh-based artist VC2art. This 18-piece collection of paintings will be displayed in a gallery-style format in the pit at Stage AE right on the north shore of downtown PGH. 

Along with these canvas paintings, there will be a live art installation that will be curated by Zack & Chase Edgar from Zeds (@shopzeds) as well as Augmented Reality sculptures designed by artist Zack Kroll (@itsbaldboy).

***ALL GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET SALES WILL GO DIRECTLY TO STEEL CITY IMPACT***

🎉 Big news from the The Pavement Group! 🎉⁣
⁣
After countless hours spent learning from our clients, fine-tuning algorithms, and perfecting our pavement preservation strategies, we're thrilled to announce the launch of our AI-driven pavement technology application Property Technologies! 🚀⁣
⁣
Our focus has always been YOU - the contractors and the commercial property owners and managers that help us drive our mission forward. And with this app, we're one step closer to enhancing the way we serve you.⁣
⁣
What’s in store for you?👇⁣
1️⃣ Streamlined processes that get you back to your families and what’s most important to you in your life faster than ever before.⁣
2️⃣ Simple and quick transfer of photos, videos, maps, plans, and pricing - reducing time spent on the mundane so you can focus on what matters most.⁣
3️⃣ Smarter project pricing based on historical data, current material prices, and more!⁣
⁣
This isn’t just another application for the construction industry, but a game-changer for The Pavement Group, as we continue to bring innovation to an industry that desperately needs it. And the best part? It's not just for desktop use but compatible with any Apple or Android device! 📱⁣
⁣
This tool will be exclusive to The Pavement Group and our dedicated 1TEAM Contractors and we are already in the process of planning a series of webinars to give you the lowdown on how it will revolutionize the way we all work together.⁣
⁣
Hundreds of exceptional contractors are already a part of our 1TEAM community, and we can't wait to let you in on all the exciting opportunities this app brings. ⁣
⁣
Stay tuned to our social channels for more updates - we can't wait to move into the future of pavement technology TOGETHER! 🌐⁣

The amount of gratitude I have for this woman is more than I could ever put into words.⁣
⁣
5.5 years ago when I decided at 38 years old to start down the path of becoming an entrepreneur most people in my life questioned my decision.⁣
⁣
We had 3 children at that time and Lori stayed home with the much harder job of taking care of them leaving us with only my income to live on. (Now you can see a little more why most people were a little concerned with my decision)⁣
⁣
But she NEVER doubted me. For the second time in our relationship she encourage me to do something that could ultimately put HER and our family at risk financially to fulfill MY dreams of becoming an entrepreneur…to have the opportunity to build a company and provide a culture in that company where people LOVED coming to work. ⁣
⁣
She told me repeatedly how much she believed in me and that as long as she had me and our kids that she would live under a bridge with us and be perfectly happy…and I knew in my heart that she meant it.⁣
⁣
This woman is the real reason behind anything we ever achieve as a family. She’s the reason I’ve never given up, never considered the option of losing, and have never had a day that I didn’t give it my absolute best. SHE deserves that for believing in me when it seemed crazy to do so. ⁣
⁣
The love I have for her is truly indescribable. She has been there for me in some of the hardest moments of my life…and has NEVER flinched. She is the real magic behind the life that we’ve built. I couldn’t show up for the people around me the way I do if SHE didn’t show up for me the way that she does. ⁣
⁣
4 kids with tons going on and she doesn’t all with no help. Drives them to/from school every day, gets them to sports, does EVERYTHING for them around the house, and plenty more that I’m not listing here. ⁣
⁣
I just wanted to share with all of you this morning what the real MVP of the Hess house does for our family. ⁣
⁣
I love you with all my heart @lorilynn777. You are truly my everything and I am so grateful that God gave me you when I needed you the most. Your love is the greatest gift of my life. ❤️
